From 558713a4214d8303c2a8152dd1059f11ca1c4fb0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 16:15:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 101/102] Phase 11 Batch 1: Coverage chapter + AI inline chips
 (data layer)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Tour generator gets two new outputs:

- A synthetic "Coverage" chapter wrapping the model's chapters
  whenever any PR file isn't referenced. File-level coverage —
  chapters carry file-level membership today, not line ranges,
  so partial-file coverage isn't expressible. Skipped when the
  model touched everything. Lives behind a stable
  `synthetic: 'coverage'` marker so callers can opt out
  (Storyboard does, in Batch 2 — Coverage has no `dependsOn` so
  it would render as a free-floating node otherwise).

- Per-chapter `chips: ChapterChip[]` — short, line-anchored
  review nudges (path, line, side, body, severity). Prompt asks
  for 0-2 per chapter. KrtPrFlatDiff renders each chip as a
  Monaco "after" injected-text decoration with a hover-message
  containing the body — decoration-only, no view zones, so it
  does not fight the auto-sized card height.

Cache normalises old v3 chapters on read by defaulting `chips`
to []; the synthetic field is undefined on old caches which is
correct. No CACHE_VERSION bump — existing PRs reopen for free,
force-refresh re-prompts to get the new fields.

Self-contained: pane.ts wiring (file tree, chip-passing in
setPullRequest, Storyboard filter) lands in Batch 2.
